TimeStamp - Class in com.wwrkds.datamodels
This is a custom class for manipulating time.

All internal calculations and outputs of the TimeStamp class are performed in UTC (GMT) time via Julian Date Number.

toTruncatedJDN() - Method in class com.wwrkds.datamodels.TimeStamp
The Truncated Julian Day (TJD) was introduced by NASA/Goddard in 1979 as part of a parallel grouped binary time code (PB-5) "designed specifically, although not exclusively, for spacecraft applications." TJD was a 4-digit day count from MJD 44000, which was May 24, 1968, represented as a 14-bit binary number.
